    <comment>- add fix-cmdline-overflow.patch: this fixes memory corruption if more than
  MAX_DEVS command line arguments are passed.

  An invocation like:

  /usr/lib/hwsupport/steamos-powerbuttond /dev/input/event0 /dev/input/event1 /dev/input/event2 /dev/input/event3 /dev/input/event4 /dev/input/event5 /dev/input/event0

  otherwise ends up in a segmentation fault or similar issues.

  Finding in the context of the review bug bsc#1249602.

  The upstream repository is only a mirror from semi-public Valve sources, so
  submitting it there doesn't seem to make sense at the moment.</comment>
